<HEADLINE> Bangladesh Observes 78th Int'l Cooperative Day </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, July 1 (Xinhua) -- The 78th International Cooperative
Day is observed in Bangladesh Saturday hailing solidarity with the
cooperators of other countries of the globe.
</P>
<P>
The Directorate of Cooperatives has taken up extensive programs
to observe the day with a renewed pledge to encourage the
cooperators toward eradication of poverty from the country by
infusing the philosophy of cooperative movement into the
conscience of the general mass.
</P>
<P>
The Rural Development and Cooperative Division and the
Directorate of Cooperatives jointly organized a discussion on the
day in the afternoon.
</P>
<P>
Bangladeshi President Shahabuddin Ahmed and Prime Minister
Sheikh Hasina in their messages on the occasion wished overall
success of the day and said the main objective of the cooperative
movement is to make everyone self-independent through united
economic activities.
</P>
<P>
They expressed the hope that the cooperative movement would
show the path toward a happy and prosperous Bangladesh as dreamt
by all Bangladeshi people. 
</P>
</TEXT>
