<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Eight Hurt in Bomb Blast on Dal Lake Bank </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
An explosive device, planted in a handcart parked near a hotel
along the bank of world famous Dal Lake, went off at around 16:45
hours when an army convoy was passing by.
</P>
<P>
Three armymen, including a junior commissioned officer were
slightly injured in the blast which was apparently aimed at their
convoy, police said, adding that five civilians, including two
women, passing by were seriously wounded.
</P>
<P>
According to the Press Trust of India, this is for the first
time in recent months that militants have targeted an area
frequented by tourists. The Boulevard Road has a stream of hotels
on one side and the Dal Lake on the other.
</P>
<P>
Minutes after the incident, militants struck in the Karan Nagar
area of Srinagar, firing six grenades at an army camp. However,
there was no loss of life or damage to the property as the devices
exploded in open area.
</P>
<P>
No militant groups has claimed responsibility for the attacks
so far. 
</P>
</TEXT>
