<HEADLINE> Indian FM Supports Palestinian Claim of Jerusalem </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GAZA, July 2 (Xinhua) -- Visiting Indian Foreign Minister
Jaswant Singh said here Sunday that Jerusalem is part of the
Israel-occupied territories, and that India supports the
Palestinians in their struggle to establish an independent state.
</P>
<P>
Singh made the remarks during his talks with Faisal al-Husseini,

a member of the Palestinian Liberation Organization (PLO) executive
committee who is in charge of the dossier of Jerusalem.
</P>
<P>
Al-Husseini briefed Singh on the situation of Jerusalem under
the Israeli occupation, and noted that the peace process between
Israel and the Palestinians urges the Israeli full withdrawal from
the occupied Palestinian territories including Jerusalem.
</P>
<P>
Al-Husseini held Israel responsible for potential reactions in
case of its refusal to to withdraw, making it certain that the
Palestinians are strong enough to notch up their national legal
rights.
</P>
<P>
He added, "Peace is our strategic option but it is not our sole
option if Israel insists on sealing off the peace road."
</P>
<P>
The Indian official, who arrived in the region on June 30 in a
historic visit to Israel and the Palestinian self-rule areas, has
signed a mechanism for bilateral cooperation for combatting
terrorism with Israeli Foreign Minister David Levy. 
</P>
</TEXT>
