<HEADLINE> Saudi FM Welcomes Sea Border Agreement With Kuwait </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT, July 2 ( Xinhua ) -- Saudi Foreign Minister Saud al-
Faisal on Sunday welcomed the signing of an agreement on
demarcation of sea borders between Kuwait and Saudi Arabia.
</P>
<P>
The agreement was inked here on Sunday by al-Faisal and Kuwaiti
First Deputy Prime Minister and Foreign Minister Sheikh Sabah al-
Ahmad al-Jaber al-Sabah on the second day of an ongoing visit by
Saudi Crown Prince Abdullah Ibn Abdul-Aziz.
</P>
<P>
In a press conference following the signing of the agreement,
Faisal said it is natural for both countries to seek to resolve any
outstanding issues between them.
</P>
<P>
Saudi Arabia and Kuwait have demarcated their land borders and
also agreed to share the stupendous oil wealth.
</P>
<P>
Several weeks ago, both countries sought to reach an agreement
on demarcating al-Garf al-Qarry area as al-Dorah oilfield exists at
al-Mothalath region between Kuwait, Saudi Arabia and Iran, which is
a point of contention with Iran.
</P>
<P>
The issue of demarcation of borders with Iran will be solved
amicably and peacefully, al-Faisal added.
</P>
<P>
Abdullah's visit had been slated for last June 12 but it was
delayed due to a visit paid by Yemeni President Abdullah Saleh to
Saudi Arabia and postponed for the second time owing to the demise
of Hafez al-Assad.
</P>
<P>
Sunday's agreement between Saudi Arabia and Kuwait came two
weeks after a treaty on demarcation of borders between Yemen and
Saudi Arabia was hammered out. 
</P>
</TEXT>
