<HEADLINE> 13 Tanzanians Missing in Boat Accident </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, July 2 (Xinhua) -- Thirteen Tanzanians are
feared to have drowned to death in the Indian Ocean after a
fishing boat capsized at a bay in Tanzania's Coast Region at dawn
on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The ill-fated vessel, christened Odysseas, had 28 passengers on
board when it overturned after being hit by a strong wave,
according to chief marine engineer Josephat Natianota of the
Tanzania Harbors Authority.
</P>
<P>
The engineer told the official Daily News on Sunday evening
that 15 people were rescued by fishermen who were in other
fishing vessels.
</P>
<P>
The survivors clutched at the vessels' life saving equipment
for some hours before they were rescued and ferried to Dar es
Salaam later in the day, said Natianota.
</P>
<P>
People feared dead include the vessels' crew, particularly
those who were in the engine room and the wheel room.
</P>
<P>
According to Natianota, divers in navy boats went to the scene
of the accident on Saturday morning in search of the missing
persons, but they could do nothing because the vessel had already
sunk in deep sea.
</P>
<P>
"Unless miracles happen, the missing persons cannot be traced
again," he added. 
</P>
