<HEADLINE> Bangladeshi Student Activist Killed in Fight </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, July 2 (Xinhua) -- An activist of the Jatiyatabadi
Chhatra Dal (Nationalist Student Party), a student front of the
Bangladesh Nationalist Party, was killed and six others received
bullet injuries Sunday as two factions of the student group fought
with each other on the Dhaka University (DU) campus.
</P>
<P>
Eye witnesses and police sources said the clash erupted when a
faction attacked its opponents' procession in the morning of the
DU campus, a hot bed of agitational politics.
</P>
<P>
They said the activist was killed when several bombs he carried
exploded in the fight.
</P>
<P>
During the fight, the two groups exploded at least 25 homemade
bombs and traded an unspecified number of gunshots, panicking
common students, said witnesses.
</P>
<P>
At an emergency meeting, the Dhaka University Syndicate decided
to suspended 20 students in connection with violent incidents on
the campus.
</P>
<P>
It also formed an inquiry committee in this connection, and
urged the law-enforcing agencies to take legal actions to help "
maintain a congenial academic atmosphere."
</P>
