<HEADLINE> Three Russian Policemen Killed in Chechnya </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, July 2 (Xinhua) -- Three Russian policemen were killed
when their patrol car hit a self-made mine in the Chechen village
of Shelkovskaya Saturday evening, reported Russian media Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The incident occurred at 20:30 Moscow time (1730 GMT) when the
three were driving their vehicle to a shooting range, located on
the western environs of the district center Shelkovskaya. At the
entrance to the shooting range, the car hit a landmine made out of
an artillery shell, and the policemen die of numerous
fragmentation wounds, Itar-Tass cited the police department of the
Russian Interior Ministry in Chechnya as saying.
</P>
<P>
Russia's RTR television announced the dead were Alexei
Moskovkin and Yuri Sverchkov of the Moscow Regional Police
Department, and Dmitri Ovdeyev of the Podolsk Police.
</P>
<P>
Russia says it has destroyed major separatist forces in
Chechnya, but rebel hit-and- run attacks cost the Russian military
several lives daily. 
</P>
