<HEADLINE> CPPCC Chairman Meets Romanian Parliamentary Delegation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 2 (Xinhua) -- Li Ruihuan, chairman of the
National Committee of the Chinese People's Political Consultative
Conference (CPPCC), met today with Mincea Ionescu-Quintus,
chairman of Romania's Senate, and his delegation.
</P>
<P>
Li said that China and Romania have a time-honored friendship,
and friendly relations between the two countries and peoples have
been developing steadily despite changes which have taken place in
the international arena and their respective countries.
</P>
<P>
He added that the main reason why the two countries have had
good relations is that they respect each other's choice of
development road, in accordance with their respective conditions,
and share the same sincere hope that the two countries may enjoy
economic development and prosperity, and that their peoples will
live happy lives.
</P>
<P>
Li said that the CPPCC and Romania's Senate play important
roles in their respective countries, and the strengthening of
exchanges between them will help promote the development of
relations between the two countries and peoples.
</P>
<P>
He also thanked the Romanian government and parliament for
their support for China on the issues of Taiwan and human rights.
</P>
<P>
Agreeing with Li's comment on bilateral relations, Ionescu-
Quintus said that a traditional Sino-Romanian friendship not only
exists between leaders of the two countries, but is also deeply
rooted in the hearts of the two peoples.
</P>
<P>
Romania is fully prepared to promote its cooperation with China
in a variety of areas, he added, expressing the belief that his
China visit would help enhance mutual trust and understanding
between the two sides.
</P>
<P>
He said that Romania supports China's policy of ``one country,
two systems," and that he believes that such a policy will be
fully successful.
</P>
<P>
The Romanian delegation arrived here this afternoon for a week-
long visit at the CPPCC's invitation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
