<HEADLINE> Vietnam's Crude Oil Export Rises Sharply in First Six Months </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, July 2 (Xinhua) -- Vietnam posted a record crude oil
export value of over 1.5 billion U.S. dollars in the first half of
the year, 88 percent higher than that of the same period last year,
Vietnam News Agency (VNA) reported Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The oil and gas sector of the country in the six months tapped
7.4 million tons of crude oil, a year-on-year rise of 1.5 percent.
</P>
<P>
The export value rose sharply due to a price hike in the
international market, said VNA, adding the average price of crude
oil in the past months stood at between 28 and 30.5 U.S.dollars
per barrel.
</P>
<P>
Apart from its traditional crude oil buyers, including Japan,
South Korea and Singapore, Vietnam has expanded its crude oil
export to new markets such as the United States, the United
Kingdom, the Netherlands, Thailand and Australia.  
