<HEADLINE> 1 Killed, 8 Injured in Ottawa Highway Collision </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, July 2 (Xinhua) -- A woman was killed and eight people
were injured late Saturday in a highway collision just out of the
urban area of Ottawa.
</P>
<P>
An eastbound mini-van carrying six people lost control and
swerved into the westbound lane to crash with an on-coming Honda
Civic on a sharp curve along Highway 7 at 4 p.m. local time,
police said.
</P>
<P>
A 35-year-old mother, who drove the Honda Civic, appeared to
have turned the car at the last second to took the full brunt of
the impact, so that her two daughters, both under 6 years old,
could survive the accident.
</P>
<P>
"The full force of the collision was on the driver's side and
the mother was killed instantly," said the police. All the others
were later sent to hospital in Ottawa after rescue teams arrived
to help them out of the twisted wreckage. 
