<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 15:30 GMT, July 2 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GAZA -- The Palestinian Liberation Organization's Central
Committee convenes here Sunday to discuss preparations for a
Palestinian state later this year.
</P>
<P>
One hundred and twenty-nine members of the committee from
various PLO factions attended the two-day meeting.
</P>
<P>
Palestinian leader Yasser Arafat has said that he is determined
to declare an independent Palestinian state with Jerusalem as its
capital this year - with or without a peace treaty with Israel. (
PLO-Statehood)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
JERUSALEM -- Preparing for a unilateral statehood declaration,
Palestinian National Authority Chairman Yasser Arafat issued an
order late last week banning departures of top PNA officials as of
next month, the Israeli daily Ha'aretz reported on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Starting August 3, top PNA officials will not be allowed to
leave PNA territories unless Arafat himself personally approves
special departure requests, the paper reported, citing a
Palestinian Liberation Organization (PLO) member. (Palestine-No-
travel Order)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
BAGHDAD -- More than 1.3 million Iraqi have died because of the
decade-old devastating U.N. embargo, Iraq's Health Ministry said
in a report released on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The report said that from August 1990 till the end of last May,
a total of 1,316,578 Iraqis perished due to the "disastrous
effects" of the embargo on Iraq's health sector. Among the victims
were 600,000 children under the age of five, it added. (Iraq-
Sanctions-Deaths)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
KAMPALA -- Ugandan President Yoweri Museveni and his Rwandan
counterpart Paul Kagame agreed on Sunday to explore ways to
improve relations between the two countries after their troops
repeatedly clashed in the northern Congolese city of Kisangani.
</P>
<P>
According to the joint communique issued at the end of the
talks in Entebbe, 40 kilometers south of the Ugandan capital
Kampala, the two leaders reiterated their strong commitment to the
Lusaka Cease-fire Agreement and resolved to work together for its
full and rapid implementation. (Uganda-Rwanda-Relations)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
JERUSALEM -- Israel is considering transferring about 1,000
former Israeli-allied South Lebanon Army (SLA) militiamen and
their family members to other countries, a Interior Ministry
official disclosed Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The first batch of such ex-SLA militiamen wanting to move
abroad will be flown to Germany next week if all bureaucratic
procedures are smooth as expected, the official said.
</P>
<P>
Israel is also conducting intensive talks with other countries,
mostly in North and South America, to persuade them to absorb some
SLA refugees. (Israel-SLA Refugees)  
</P>
