<HEADLINE> Coulthard Wins French Grand Prix </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, July 2 (Xinhua) -- David Coulthard of Britain won the
first place while teammate Mika Hakkinen of Finland finished
second as McLaren team scored a 1-2 finish in the Formula One
racing's French Grand Prix in Magny-Cours, France, on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Rubens Barrichello, driving a Ferrari, placed third but the
driver of the other Ferrari, Michael Schumacher, had to retire
from the race with engine problem.
</P>
<P>
Coulthard earned 10 points from this victory and cut the margin
behind championship leader Schumacher to 12 points. Coulthard had
won the British and Monaco Grand Prix earlier this season.
</P>
<P>
Former world champion Jacques Villeneuve finished fourth in a
BAR, Ralf Schumacher was fifth in a Williams and Jarno Trulli in a
Jordan finished sixth.
</P>
<P>
With the 17-race season now in its second half, Coulthard has
44 points, while Schumacher leads with 56. Hakkinen remained third
with 38. 
</P>
