<HEADLINE> Three More Boat Tragedy Corpses Recovered </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHENGDU, July 2 (Xinhua) -- Three more bodies from the boat
tragedy which occurred on the Yangtze River on June 22 were
recovered today, bringing the confirmed death toll from the
accident to 126.
</P>
<P>
According to a report reaching here today, four people are
still missing. The search and rescue operation is continuing.
</P>
<P>
Rescuers have salvaged 130 bodies from the river since June 22.
However, four of them were identified by forensic experts as not
victims of the boat disaster.
</P>
<P>
The passenger vessel Rong Jian, which was designed to carry a
maximum of 101 people, had 221 passengers on board when it hit a
rock and sank while sailing in foggy conditions.
</P>
<P>
Each victim's family has been given 6,000 yuan (about 725 U.S.
dollars) in compensation, and more compensation is to be earmarked
for them, said Hu Ruquan, deputy head of Hejiang County, the
native place of most of the victims. 
