<HEADLINE> URGENT: Uganda Ruling Movement Wins in Referendum </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, July 2 (Xinhua) -- Ugandans overwhelmingly favored
retaining the current National Resistance Movement as the
country's political system as opposed to a multi party system,
results announced on Sunday shows.
</P>
<P>
According to the final official result, the ruling National
Resistance Movement won 4.32 million or 90.7 percent of the votes
cast in the June 29 referendum, with only 442,000 or 9.3 percent
of votes for multi party system.
</P>
<P>
About 4.9 million or 51.1 percent of 9.6 million registered
voters cast ballots in close to 16,500 polling stations across the
east African country. 
</P>
