<HEADLINE> Jet Carrying Philippine Cabinet Members Loses Pressure </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, July 2 (Xinhua) -- A jet carrying five Philippine
cabinet members suddenly lost pressure due to a door seal leak
while flying to Manila from a southern city on Saturday night, and
landed safely in Manila later, a government official said Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The plane carried Public Works secretary Gregorio Vigilar,
Agrarian Reform secretary Horacio Morales, and three other
officials of cabinet rank who accompanied President Joseph Estada
in a visit to Davao,said Press undersecretary Icasiano Guetierrez,
who was also aboard the plane.
</P>
<P>
Estrada left Davao on another plane, he said in a statement.
</P>
<P>
Gutierrez said they were flying in stormy weather over
Marinduque when they heard a loud thud near the plane door
followed by a sudden lost of plane pressure.
</P>
<P>
"The plane bobbed up and down, almost losing control. The
pilots hurriedly reached out for the emergency oxygen masks and
the emergency book manual,'' he said in a statement.
</P>
<P>
The pilots brought the plane from 18,000 feet to 11,000 feet to
stabilize the plane with a red emergency light continuously
flashing in the cabin, he added.
</P>
<P>
Last April, a Boeing jet slammed into a tree-covered hill on
Samal island near the Davao airport in the southern Philippines,
killing all 131 people aboard in the country's worst air disaster.
</P>
</TEXT>
