<HEADLINE> Survey Into Sea Waters Near Pearl River Estuary </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, July 2 (Xinhua) -- A comprehensive survey of the
marine environment near the Pearl River estuary, a Sino-Japanese
governmental cooperation project, has been launched in south China
's Guangdong Province.
</P>
<P>
The Pearl River estuary and its nearby waters have become some
of the worst-polluted sea waters in China. Due to a shortage of
funds for the work, the problem has long gone un-checked.
</P>
<P>
According to the new agreement, the Japanese government will
contribute 20 million yuan (about 2.41 million U.S. dollars) to
the survey project.
</P>
<P>
The survey will take two years to finish, according to members
of the survey team.
</P>
<P>
The survey is to determine the nature and scope of anti-
pollution measures necessary in the estuary area. 
</P>
