<HEADLINE> New Zealand Holds Chinese Film Festival </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WELLINGTON, July 2 (Xinhua) -- The 2000 Chinese Film Festival,
organized by the Film Bureau of the People's Republic of China and
sponsored by the Asia 2000 Foundation of New Zealand and the
Pacific Culture and Arts Exchange Center, began in New Zealand on
Sunday.
</P>
<P>
During the festival, which will be held from June 2 to August
16 in Auckland, Hamilton, Wellington, Dunedin and Christchurch,
about 10 outstanding Chinese films will be shown. They include "At
the Crossroads," "A New Year Sacrifice," "Early Spring," "Genghis
Khan," "The Road Home" and "Emergency Landing."
</P>
<P>
The films, whose production spanned more than half a century,
reflect the history and achievements of the Chinese film-making
industry. 
</P>
