<HEADLINE> World Famous Real Estate Brokerage Eyes China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 2 (Xinhua) -- Century 21 Real Estate Corp, one of
the world's largest franchisers of residential real estate
brokerage offices, plans to set up a nationwide first-owner and
secondary real estate network for Chinese customers.
</P>
<P>
According to Business Weekly of China Daily, Century 21 will
also open the first office in Beijing in July.
</P>
<P>
The goal of Century 21 China is to grant franchises in 30
regions, to develop 2,000 offices and train 14,000 professional
agents in China, said Harry Lu, president of Century 21 Real
Estate China.
</P>
<P>
"China's accession to the World Trade Organization will bring
us more opportunities in our business expansion," he said.
</P>
<P>
Lu said that China's real estate market has slowed in recent
years, overheating has disappeared and the markets are now more
stable.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese government is making progress in improving market
regulation, but this is a long road with many hurdles to be
overcome, he said.
</P>
<P>
China's housing reform which has abolished the welfare housing
distribution system has thrown millions of people into the real
estate market.
</P>
<P>
Most of these people know little about the real estate market,
Lu said. "They need qualified agents to help them and Century 21
will try to regularize the intermediary market," he added.
</P>
