<HEADLINE> Inflation Rises in India </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Inflation level rose by 0.07 percentage points during the week
to 6.28 percent from the level of 6.21 percent in the previous
week, mainly due to an increase in the non-food articles like
sunflower and kardi seeds, said the release.
</P>
<P>
India's inflation during the corresponding week of last year
was only 1.99 percent.
</P>
<P>
The index for all commodities during the week ended June 17
rose by 0.1 percent to 152.4 as against 152.2 in the previous week,
the release added. 
</P>
