studies in Japan next year.
</P>
<P>
The Matsushita Scholarship, set up by the Japan-based
Matsushita Industrial Co., Ltd. in 1998, sponsors students from
China and southeast Asian nations for further study in Japan.
</P>
<P>
So far, 24 Chinese students have won the scholarship.
</P>
<P>
 Chinese Language Education Base for Overseas Chinese
</P>
<P>
Nanjing Normal University (NNU) has become a base of Chinese
language education for overseas Chinese approved by the Office of
Overseas Chinese Affairs of the State Council.
</P>
<P>
Overseas Chinese can apply for undergraduate, graduate and
doctorate program at the University in subjects such as Chinese
Language and traditional Chinese literature. NNU will also write
the teaching materials for related subjects, train teachers for
overseas Chinese schools, and host summer camps for overseas
Chinese students.
</P>
<P>
IBM, Xiamen University Train E-Commerce Students
</P>
<P>
Xiamen University in east China's Fujian Province and IBM will
work together to train students in e-commerce.
</P>
<P>
An agreement to this effect was signed in this port city
recently, under which the two sides will co-operate in training,
program development and scientific research.
</P>
<P>
IBM has already signed similar agreements with Fudan University,
Zhejiang University, South China University of Science and
Engineering, Zhongshan University and Xi'an University in this
regard.
</P>
</TEXT>
