<DATE_TIME> 2000-07-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Sri Lanka Earns More From Tea Exports </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Total exports of tea in the January-May period of this year
made up 109.9 million kilograms from 105.8 million kilograms in
the same period last year, according to the latest statistics of
Sri Lankan Tea Board.
</P>
<P>
The tea exports also fetched prices thanks to their better
quality, the tea board sources said.
</P>
<P>
The average unit Free on Board price was 1.45 U.S. dollars per
kilogram this year from 1.39 U.S.dollars last year.
</P>
<P>
Russia and Commonwealth of Independent State countries were the
number one buyers of Sri Lanka's tea, followed by United Arab
Emirates. The other top buyers of Sri Lanka's tea for the first
five months of this year are Turkey, Syria, Iran, Egypt, Iraq,
Tunisia,Jordan and Japan.
</P>
<P>
Tea is one of Sri Lanka's main export items and the sources of
about 25 percent of its export earnings. The total tea exports
last year were over 270 million kilograms. 
</P>
</TEXT>
