<HEADLINE> Weekly Review of Regional News in China (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING: China will soon use optically variable ink (OVI) in
producing its Renminbi currency, which will enable people to pick
out a fake 100 yuan note at a glance. The ink will make colors of
the note change from light green to darker green or nearly black
when viewed from different angles.
</P>
<P>
The Beijing Municipal government has decided to renovate all
the cultural relics under municipal protection so as to preserve
them better. The work will take three years and cost about 330
million yuan (some 40 million US dollars). There are now 264 major
cultural relics in Beijing, five of which have been put on UNESCO'
s World Cultural Heritage list.
</P>
<P>
Germany's Siemens company will invest 1.5 billion U.S. dollars
in Asia by 2003 to exploit the largest potential market for mobile
business solutions. The investment plan was announced in Beijing
on June 26. Mobile business is based on the integration of
electronic business, mobile communications and IP-based networks.
</P>
<P>
"My Father Deng Xiaoping in the Cultural Revolution," a
comprehensive biography written by Deng's daughter Maomao has come
off the press on June 27 in Beijing. The book gives a biographical
account of Deng Xiaoping during the Cultural Revolution (1966-1976)
. Maomao is Deng's youngest daughter.
</P>
<P>
Beijing's three subway lines, the No.1 subway line, the loop
line and the Fuxingmen-Bawangfen line, were linked together on
June 28. Beijing has 54 km of subways, transporting about 500
million passengers a year.
