<HEADLINE> THAI Voted as World Outstanding Airline </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, July 2 (Xinhua) -- The Thai Airways International Plc.
(THAI), Thailand's national carrier, has been voted by
international passengers as the world's outstanding airline,
according to a report of THAI available here on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Over 150,000 international passengers, who were interviewed
recently, ranked THAI to the honorable status, the report said.
</P>
<P>
The result came from a survey, conducted by an international
agency -- In-flight Research Survey (IRS), which was aimed at
seeking world passengers' opinion on the development of quality
and services provided by international airlines.
</P>
<P>
The selection was based on assessments of quality and
impression of services THAI and its staff have provided to
passengers either when they were on board, or when they were at
international airports.
</P>
<P>
Given the criteria, THAI beats over 150 other world carriers in
the recent IRS survey as the world's outstanding airline, the
report noted. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
