<HEADLINE> 8 Killed, 30 Injured at Rock Festival in Denmark </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HELSINKI, July 1 (Xinhua) -- Eight people were crushed to death
and 30 others injured at midnight Friday at a Rock festival in
Roskilde, Denmark, the Finnish News Agency reported Saturday.
</P>
<P>
When the popular U.S. band Pearl Jam started performing, the
audience swarmed forward to the stage, apparently because the
microphones were placed too far from the stage, a witness was
quoted as saying.
</P>
<P>
The victims slipped or fell in front of the stage and were
trampled to death, despite the fact that various precautions
measures were taken, said local police and the festival organizers.
More rails were placed at the stage and more people were deployed
to keep order, they said.
</P>
<P>
The band was shocked by the tragedy. "This is so painful,"
Pearl Jam said.
</P>
<P>
As a result of the incident, a performance scheduled for Sunday
in Belgium was canceled.
</P>
<P>
The annual Roskilde festival has run for 30 years. More than
110,000 rock music fans have come to the festival this year from
Nordic and western Europe.
</P>
<P>
After the tragedy, the main festival stage was closed, but
performance on other stages will continue. 
</P>
</TEXT>
