<HEADLINE> Terrace Collapse Kills One, Injures Dozens in U.S. </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, July 1 (Xinhua) -- At least one person was killed
and dozens were injured as a cement terrace loaded with tourists
collapsed Saturday at an island winery in Lake Erie in Ohio, the
United States, the Associated Press reported.
</P>
<P>
The cement floor of the lakefront terrace at Lonz Winery fell
six to nine meters into an empty wine cellar. the news agency said.
</P>
<P>
One of the victims was confirmed dead, and eight of the most
seriously injured were flown by helicopter to St. Vincent Medical
Center in Toledo, AP said. It quoted a hospital spokeswoman as
saying that five of them were in a critical condition.
</P>
<P>
The terrace overlooking Lake Erie was part of the winery's
century-old main building. The winery, no longer operational for
more than 20 years, is an attractive tourism venue during summer
times, AP said. 
</P>
